    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p>
                    <bibl><ptr target="#robinson1913"/>, n. <citedRange>41</citedRange>, fig. 30</bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#Sammelbuch"/> <citedRange>5887</citedRange></bibl>; 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#DGE"/> <citedRange>231,9</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>010100</citedRange></bibl>.
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#santucci-uhlenbrock2013"/>, p. <citedRange>12</citedRange> (identification of the tomb)</bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#cdl2013"/>, p. <citedRange>186</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/>μὴ <w lemma="ἀνοίγω">ἀν<lb n="2" break="no"/>οίγεν</w>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Ne pas ouvrir.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Do not open.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Non aprire.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>لا تفتح (تحذير).</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>The ending <foreign xml:lang="grc">-εν</foreign> for active infinitive is a regular feature in the local dialect.</p>
                <p>This formula aims at protecting the recess in this chamber-tomb, which can be identified after <bibl><ptr target="#santucci-uhlenbrock2013"/></bibl>
                    from the long delated publication of Norton's final report.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
